
Medical therapy for cardiac zzso is still to a large extent based on empirical zzso Assessing and evaluating different zzso strategies constitutes the starting point for inducing decision methods to select the appropriate regimen for an individual zzso We designed a computer-based system that establishes a set of zzso rules linking attributes in a data base of patients with rhythm zzso A feasibility analysis conducted on a small set of 23 patients indicated that constraints on the number of attributes and their clinical zzso together with a representation scheme for zzso changes have to be incorporated to provide for a useful and efficient zzso 

